div.p:
On the day following news of Jessie's death, John James wrote to George Gray (1798-1877), 
                    who was a family friend and solicitor in Perth, a member of Writers to the Signet, to take responsibility 
                    for his three nephews and niece--the survivors of Jessie and Patrick's ten children. The niece, 
                    Mary Richardson (1815-49), would be taken into the family around 15 July, when the Ruskins returned home 
                    (Burd, introduction to Dearden, ed., Tour to the Lakes in Cumberland, 7; 
                    Burd, ed. Ruskin Family Letters, 1:197-98 n. 1; 
                    and see Jessie Richardson [1783-1828]).
